eply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Cash, don't care about exp</span><hr size=1> Well I hit L. 44 and I'm making a bard alt just to take a break from my mage. I don't really care about exp for now, just looking for zones/mobs I can farm for money. Any ideas?<br>
<br>
Oh yeah and are there any zones where I can get some good armor for the bard? I mean solo-able mobs.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kpm2k>kpm2k</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.faceoff.com/media/pics/200211063895673-F.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/03 3:36:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=72.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RM</span><hr size=1> 44 Mage -&gt; Goto Rathe Mountains .. kill Hill Giants, keep the Lambent stones you get from Hill Giants for the LAmbent Armor quests for your Bard.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailurya@themagicianstower>Ailurya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 5:41:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=72.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RM</span><hr size=1> Or if you don't like the KS-ing and arguing in RM, Nurga might be an option; at least from 44-46 you'll get some XP (mobs will be low dark blues to light blues), plus Chardok faction and a decent amount of cash... my Necro made around 200pp an hour there at a guess, between cash drops, FS weapons and gems; warders regularly drop opals for about 16pp each and sometimes drop a shroud of nature that sells for 200pp upwards in the Bazaar. 44 will be a little tricky, but at 45 you should be able to single-pull from two-goblin spawns most of the time, and an air pet should keep casters stunned.<br>
<br>
You'll also pick up goblin skins and mineral salts which you can probably sell for at least 10-20pp each in the Bazaar to people eager to raise Chardok faction without mass slaughter of goblins (I've seen people charging 100+, but doubt they sell many at that price). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dranglor>Dranglor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 2:55:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=72.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cash, don't care about exp</span><hr size=1> OK, for cash AND xp - OT rules.  From the PoK book, go S and E. Look for what seems to be cliffs/pits with sandy floors.  mobs you are looking for are scorpikis.  Summon pet, buff pet etc.  pull mob with a) small nuke or b) pet attack (if it's off by itself).  I recommend using the small nuke, then running a bit to get it off the paths.  They have VERY low HP, but they Harm Touch, so make sure to get the pet to take that hit.  Try not to start any fight with your pet below 80% as an add will be fatal to your pet.  Drops - up to 4p plus change, STACKABLE scorpikis venoms worth 34pp a stack w/ decent cha.  Also the scrounger scorpikis drops one of the coins for the bard drum FV quest.<br>
<br>
For just cash... summon up a pet and go smacking through the gobbies of Sol A.  Have plenty of dimensional holes available.  While camping the blazing elementals for Power of Fire, I'd kill all the gobs there, in kindle's room, in captian's room, and on the path to gnomes.  Then sell to gnomes. Rinse and repeat.  Drops - Flame Agate (stacks) - 10p, Large HQ Ore - 10p, FS weapons- 5p, Unrefined Large ore 4p, HQ small ore- 3p, unrefined small ore 3p, fiery ore 1p, plus named drops - Efreeti, Captain, Kindle... I don't recall off my head, but you can look them up, also might get an Epic sub-piece if you get lucky. <p>Bentareth<br>
